column6: Description
Newspaper of September 9, 1960, discussing Hurricane Donna heading for the Florida Keys and evacuation.
Newspaper of September 13, 1960, discussing the damages of Hurricane Donna and federal assistance.
Document about plans for first time Old Naples historic homes tour and the interest in having it.
Volume 54, no. 4 of Florida Health Notes on Hurricane Donna. Document discussing the hurricane's path and damages. The notes discuss possible health hazards in the hurricane's aftermath.

column2: Donna Was the Worst Storm We Ever Had
column6: Document looking back at Hurricane Donna's impact on Collier County including preparations for the storm and the damages.
Document discusses a hurricane photographic exhbit about hurricanes affecting Collier County from 1873 to 1960.
